## Bezel vs Prong: The Setting Decision for Pear Earrings

Pear diamonds have a pointed tip. That tip is the most fragile structural point on the stone. In a ring, this matters greatly — the hand contacts surfaces constantly. In a stud earring, the tip faces outward and contacts very little, but it is still exposed to hair, scarves, and collars.

**Prong setting:** V-prong at the tip plus three or four additional prongs around the perimeter. Maximum stone visibility. The classic, bridal-adjacent look. Slightly more delicate tip exposure than bezel. Correct choice for formal wear and buyers who prioritize sparkle over long-term durability.

**Bezel setting:** Metal rim surrounds the entire stone perimeter including the tip. Reduces stone visibility slightly at the edges. Creates a modern, finished look. Tip is fully protected. Correct choice for everyday wear, active lifestyles, and buyers who want their earrings to outlast the trend cycle.

The price difference between bezel and prong at the same carat is narrow in lab and moderate in natural. The [Bezel Lab 1 CTW at $1,410](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/bezel-stud-earrings-with-1-ctw-pear-shaped-lab-grown-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297387?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) vs. the [Prong Lab 1 CTW at $828](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251889?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational): a $582 upgrade for a daily-wear lifetime of tip protection. For buyers who will wear these earrings every single day, the bezel is worth every dollar of the upgrade.

