## Expert Summary

**What they are:** Pear shaped diamond earrings use a teardrop-silhouette brilliant-cut diamond — wider at the base, tapering to a point — in studs, drops, huggies, hoops, and statement designs. Blue Nile carries 60+ distinct pear earring styles from $438 to $14,430.

**Who should buy:** Anyone who wants more visual presence than round studs at the same carat. The pear's elongated face-up area is 8–12% larger than a round of identical weight, and the teardrop silhouette is immediately recognizable in a way round studs are not.

**Key decision sequence:** (1) Set your per-ear carat goal, double it for CTW. (2) Choose bezel (daily wear, protected tip) or prong (maximum sparkle, traditional look). (3) Lab (3× the carat for the same price) or natural (provenance, investment). Metal choice is the final and least consequential decision.

**Bottom line:** [Lab Prong 1 CTW White Gold at $828](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/pear-cut-lab-grown-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251889?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the benchmark. [Bezel Lab 1 CTW White Gold at $1,410](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/bezel-stud-earrings-with-1-ctw-pear-shaped-lab-grown-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297387?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the daily-wear upgrade. [Bezel Natural 1 CTW Platinum at $5,500](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/bezel-diamond-stud-earrings-with-1-ctw-pear-shaped-diamonds-in-platinum-item-297333?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the heirloom pick.

